            "text": "ROOT",
            "relation": "null"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Ig heavy chain class switching is directed by cytokines",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "inducing transcription from unrearranged CH genes . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Subsequently , such primed cells can undergo switch recombination",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "to express the selected new isotype . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "In the case of IgE class switching , IL-4 activates the IgE germline promoter",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "by inducing the interaction of the transcription factor STAT6 ( IL-4STAT ) with a responsive DNA element in the proximal region of the promoter . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This study describes the characterization of two additional cis-acting elements",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that interact with members of the NF kappa B/rel transcription factor family in an IL-4-independent fashion . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Electrophoretic mobility shift assays show that the nucleoprotein complex",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "formed on the upstream site ( NF kappa B1 )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "contains the classical p50/p65 heterodimer . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "The complex on the proximal site ( NF kappa B2 ) appears to be composed of p50 and relB . <S>",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "IgE germline promoter reporter gene constructs",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "carrying point mutations in the NF kappa B2 site",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "were largely unresponsive to IL-4 stimulation in transient transfection experiments ,",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "while plasmids with similar mutations in the NF kappa B1 site responded to cytokine stimulation better than the wild-type promoter . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "The NF kappa B2 effect was dependent on the presence of the STAT6 binding site ,",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "demonstrating that the NF kappa B2 motif is necessary but not sufficient for mediating cytokine up-regulation . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "In addition , the combination of a NF kappa B/rel binding site and the STAT6 response element conferred IL-4 inducibility to a heterologous minimal promoter ,",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "while the individual sites had no effect . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The available data suggest that the NF kappa B2 nucleoprotein complex may cooperate with DNA-bound STAT6",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "to achieve IL-4-dependent activation of the human IgE germline gene . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        }
    ]
}